<section id="problem-statement" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">

    <!-- Title -->
    <h2 class="section-heading">
      Sensor-to-Decision Bottleneck in Agentic Autonomy
    </h2>

    <!-- 🔥 NEW: Highlighted Intro Box -->
    <div class="intro-box">
      <p>
        Agentic AI robots increasingly couple high-rate multimodal sensing with learned perception and foundation-model reasoning, yet deployment failures arise from a <strong>sensor-to-decision bottleneck</strong>, not weak models.
        Even with high per-frame accuracy, decisions fail when not grounded in <strong>fresh, decision-time evidence</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 🔥 Key Problems -->
    <!-- Item 1 -->
<div class="highlight-item">
  <div class="highlight-icon">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <path d="M3 12h18M3 6h18M3 18h18"/>
    </svg>
  </div>
  <div class="highlight-content">
    <h4>Stale Decision Inputs</h4>
    <p>Queueing delays force decisions on outdated sensor evidence despite high model accuracy.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Item 2 -->
<div class="highlight-item">
  <div class="highlight-icon">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/>
      <path d="M12 7v5l3 3"/>
    </svg>
  </div>
  <div class="highlight-content">
    <h4>Low-Value Data Overload</h4>
    <p>Redundant and vibration-amplified streams saturate onboard pipelines and waste compute.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Item 3 -->
<div class="highlight-item">
  <div class="highlight-icon">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24">
      <polyline points="4 17 10 11 13 14 20 7"/>
    </svg>
  </div>
  <div class="highlight-content">
    <h4>Delayed Informative Evidence</h4>
    <p>High-value frames arrive too late, degrading real-time decision reliability.</p>
  </div>
</div>

    <!-- 🔥 Bridge -->
    <div class="bridge-text">
      <p>
        <strong>SenseGuard</strong> addresses this gap by treating robustness as a 
        <strong>decision-time freshness objective</strong>, combining adaptive filtering with model-centric data curation. This design ensures decisions use the most informative, up-to-date sensory evidence rather than stale inputs.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>



